Victorian Football Association

Season 1888

 

Season Notes

Premiership to be decided by Proportional Points system commencing this season (VFA Meeting 7 October 1887)

Minimum games to qualify for the Premiership is 18.

Only games played from May onwards counted by Association towards the Premiership.

Amalgamation of Williamstown and South Williamstown Football Clubs agreed at a meeting of the Williamstown Football Club and Williamstown Cricket Club on Wed 8 Feb 1888.

St Kilda and Prahran Football Clubs amalgamated and played as St Kilda in 1888 Season.

Permission granted by the Association for Hotham to change its name to North Melbourne (VFA Meeting 20 April 1888)

Notes:

- Teams ranked by Proportional Points. Minimum of 18 games required to qualify for the Premiership.

- Ballarat, South Ballarat, Footscray, Ballarat Imperial and University failed to play 18 games and therefore do not rank on the final premiership ladder

- Behinds were recorded but did not count towards the final score or in determining the result of matches.

- The percentage column is an indication only. Teams finishing with equal proportional points were deemed to have achieved an equal finishing position on the final ladder.
